#compdef js-compute-runtime js-compute
# =============================================================================
# js-compute-runtime — Fastly Inc.'s "JavaScript SDK and
#                      runtime for building Fastly Compute
#                      applications" — the official CLI
#                      that takes a JavaScript / TypeScript
#                      source file as input and produces
#                      a single self-contained
#                      WebAssembly module (.wasm) suitable
#                      for deployment to Fastly Compute@
#                      Edge (Fastly's commercial
#                      edge-computing platform built on
#                      wasmtime + WASI).  The toolchain
#                      bundles SpiderMonkey (the
#                      Mozilla JavaScript engine) as
#                      WebAssembly, pre-initializes it
#                      with the user's JS via Bytecode
#                      Alliance's Wizer (covered Axis 33
#                      Rust side R721's wasmtime
#                      ecosystem), and optionally AOT-
#                      compiles via Weval, producing
#                      sub-millisecond cold-start WASM
#                      functions deployable to Fastly's
#                      global CDN.
#                      Distinguishing from Cloudflare
#                      Workers (V8 isolates, not WASM),
#                      Vercel Edge Functions (V8 isolates),
#                      Deno Deploy (V8), AWS Lambda
#                      (containers + Firecracker microVMs),
#                      Lagon (defunct V8-based edge),
#                      and spin (Fermyon's WASM FaaS) by:
#                        - SPIDERMONKEY-IN-WASM RUNTIME
#                          — Fastly bundles the
#                          SpiderMonkey JS engine
#                          compiled to WASM as fastly.wasm;
#                          user JS code runs inside this
#                          WASM-hosted JS engine, giving
#                          true V8-compatible JS semantics
#                          on the edge
#                        - WIZER PRE-INITIALIZATION —
#                          uses @bytecodealliance/wizer
#                          (the same Bytecode Alliance
#                          Wizer used by ambient at R721)
#                          to pre-initialize the WASM
#                          module at build time; user JS
#                          is parsed + loaded + heap-
#                          serialized into the WASM
#                          before deployment, reducing
#                          cold-start from ~100ms to
#                          <1ms
#                        - WEVAL AOT — `--enable-aot`
#                          uses @bytecodealliance/weval
#                          (Whole-program Evaluation)
#                          for ahead-of-time
#                          compilation of WASM-hosted JS
#                          to native machine code at
#                          build time; significant
#                          performance improvement at
#                          cost of larger binary
#                        - JCO INTEGRATION — uses
#                          @bytecodealliance/jco (BA's
#                          JavaScript Component Model
#                          tooling, headline of Axis 33
#                          TS-Node companion role; see
#                          taxonomy notes below) for
#                          WebAssembly Component Model
#                          integration + WIT binding
#                          generation
#                        - HTTP-CACHE-AWARE — `--enable-
#                          http-cache` enables Fastly's
#                          HTTP cache hook API for
#                          request/response interception
#                        - HIGH-RES TIME METHODS —
#                          `--enable-experimental-high-
#                          resolution-time-methods`
#                          unlocks sub-millisecond
#                          timestamps (fastly.now())
#                          for performance measurement;
#                          standard Date.now() is rounded
#                          for fingerprinting protection
#                        - TOP-LEVEL AWAIT — `--enable-
#                          experimental-top-level-await`
#                          enables ES2022 top-level
#                          await in user JS modules
#                        - ESBUILD BUNDLER — uses
#                          esbuild for fast multi-file
#                          JavaScript bundling before
#                          handing off to the WASM
#                          compilation pipeline
#                        - COSMICONFIG — uses cosmiconfig
#                          for `.fastly.toml`/.fastly.
#                          json` config file discovery
#                        - SDK METADATA — embedded SDK
#                          metadata field in produced
#                          WASM for Fastly's deployment
#                          analytics
#                        - MULTI-NAME BINARY — published
#                          npm package `@fastly/js-
#                          compute` provides two bin
#                          aliases: `js-compute` (short)
#                          + `js-compute-runtime` (full)
#                      Used by: Fastly Compute@Edge
#                      developers (Fastly's commercial
#                      edge computing product), full-
#                      stack engineers wanting V8-
#                      compatible JS at the edge with
#                      WASM isolation, JAMstack +
#                      Jamstack architects building
#                      personalized edge logic, and
#                      performance researchers studying
#                      sub-millisecond cold start WASM
#                      FaaS patterns.
