# WHY @bytecodealliance/jco IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-33 TS-NODE CHOICE:
#
#   @bytecodealliance/jco ("JavaScript Component Model toolchain", aka
#   "jco") is the Bytecode Alliance's official JavaScript tooling for
#   the WebAssembly Component Model.  Built on top of wasmtime
#   (covered Axis 33 Rust side) + the Bytecode Alliance's broader
#   WASM toolchain.  Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. COMPONENT MODEL FIRST-CLASS — primary tool for working with
#        WASM Components in JavaScript; transpile Components to
#        regular ECMAScript modules + bundle WIT bindings
#     2. PREVIEW2-SHIM — companion package @bytecodealliance/
#        preview2-shim provides WASI Preview 2 polyfills in JS
#        runtime
#     3. WIT BINDING GENERATION — `jco guest-types <wit-file>` +
#        `jco types <wit-file>` produce TypeScript type definitions
#        from WIT (WebAssembly Interface Types) declarations
#     4. TRANSPILATION — `jco transpile <component.wasm>` converts
#        a Component to ES modules that can be imported into Node
#        / Deno / Bun / browsers
#     5. RUN MODE — `jco run <component.wasm>` executes a WASM
#        Component using the Bytecode Alliance JS runtime;
#        functionally equivalent to wasmtime's `wasmtime run` for
#        Component Model WASM
#     6. BACKED BY BCA — the Bytecode Alliance's flagship JS tooling
#        for WASM beyond the browser; corporate-funded development +
#        long-term roadmap
#     7. ~954+ STARS on bytecodealliance/jco
#     8. USED BY FASTLY — js-compute-runtime specifically depends
#        on jco for Component Model integration; visible in
#        package.json
#     9. TYPESCRIPT-NATIVE — written in TypeScript; provides
#        TypeScript types for all WIT-derived bindings
#    10. CORE TO COMPONENT MODEL ECOSYSTEM — without jco, the JS
#        ecosystem cannot meaningfully consume WASM Components
